-- New South Wales State Approves A$785 Million Mount Arthur Coal Expansion
-- B y   G a r f i e l d   R e y n o l d s
-- 2010-09-24T09:35:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/new-south-wales-state-approves-a-785-million-mount-arthur-coal-expansion.html
The government of New South Wales
state approved a $A785 million expansion to the Mount Arthur
Coal mine in the Hunter Valley region north of sydney.  The project will expand the mine’s output to 36 million
metric tons a year for a period of 12 years, from 28 million
tons a year, the government said today in a statement.
Melbourne-based BHP Billiton Ltd., the world’s largest mining
company, lists Mount Arthur as one of its operations on the
company’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
